<br>
Use it for down time, keep regen up, stone down, rest. <p><p align=left><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide CoGuildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/changingtide/images/inpom.jpg><br><b>"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"You must do the thing you think you cannot do." - Eleanor Roosevelt </font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upaldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/4/01 8:37:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hunting with Manastone</span><hr size=1> Best for players with 2 accounts/ 2 PCs (1 Primary Castor, 1 Level 39+ Cleric for CHeal).<br>
<br>
Have either character stone down to 5% then Cheal (Have Symbol on Both).  <br>
<br>
Otherwise you are going to want to have some form of 'free' healing... Vellious BP, ES BP, ES Legs, Fungi Tunic...<br>
<br>
If you have to pay to keep your own Regen up, it really only works out to about 3 mana per tick extra. (Comparing the mana gained, versus the mana spent casting regen).<br>
